description: Traces of incised decoration in middle of face.  This tapers from centre.  Is sharp edge & butt.  The widest part of side is plain, but between middle and edge there is a suggestion of facets on the sides.  Ripples are not so cleanly defined on reverse. The 2 raised lines (running across ripples) are from the mould.  There is another, much shorter, slanting in from the edge.
publications: Hemp, Arch. Camb., 1924, 329-331, Figs. 2,3 ;, , Megan & Hartley, Pr. Prehist. Soc., 1938, no. 23
remarks: It has been said that these ripples form a decoration, but they may have been caused by the molten metal being poured into a cold mould.
